  "text": "Isobologram analysis was used to investigate the interaction effect (synergistic, antagonistic, or additive interaction) between different binary combinations. Sets of equally effective concentrations were selected to generate isobolograms according to the method described in a previous study [CITATION_1] . The IC 50 of each single antimicrobial was used to draw an additive line between the combined antimicrobials. Reduction of antimicrobials was calculated according to:",
